The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Friday, December 26, 2003 				 PMK sticks to coalition
																								Chennai, Dec. 25: The Pattali Makkal Katchi today broke ranks with the DMK, refusing to follow it out of the National Democratic Alliance government at the Centre, reports our special correspondent.																								The DMK quit the NDA last Saturday, increasing the pressure on the PMK to follow. But PMK founder leader S. Ramadoss today said: The PMK has decided to continue to be part of the (A.B.) Vajpayee-led NDA government in the hope and expectation that he will fulfil all our long-pending demands in the days to come.																								The leader made his announcement at a crowded news conference here this evening after a one-hour meeting of the PMKs high-powered political affairs committee, called to discuss the DMK move.																								The PMK, which has five Lok Sabha MPs, has two Union ministers  minister of state for food processing .T. Shanmugham and minister of state for railways A.K. Murthy. Both were present along with other MPs, MLAs and PMK chief G.K. Mani at todays meeting. 
